        <p>Since using visualization tools can be
      processor intensive, there are two check boxes on the bottom right to
      toggle the updating of the two smaller views. This way you can
      watch playbacks in the main view at a faster rate. It can also be to set
      specific views to one time frame and a different view to a different time frame
      and view the difference in depth and magnitude between the two.
      <br/>
      <br/>
      While playbacks are running the user can still interact with the program. They can use mouse interactions
      as well as change depth, magnitude, color, and year values. Finally while its running you can even
      enable or disable the smaller views.
      </p>
